text:
HTC Ocean Note to reportedly launch as the 6-inch HTC U Ultra HTC Ocean Note to reportedly launch as the 6-inch HTC U Ultra By January 2, 2017 “HTC’s upcoming phablet is expected to launch on January 12th” 
HTC has been in the news lately for the rumoured launch of its Ocean Note smartphone. While the recently leaked render revealed that that the smartphone will ship with a headphone jack, new reports claim that the same might not be the case. Got it from an unverified source but I put that here anyway… ? #HTC Ocean Note = HTC U Ultra = 6″ display = no 3.5mm Jack… — OnLeaks (@OnLeaks) December 31, 2016 
Reported by reliable tipster OnLeaks , the HTC Ocean Note will sport a 6-inch display and won’t ship with a headphone jack. The leakster also stated that the smartphone will make its debut under the HTC U Ultra moniker, in line with HTC’s January 12th launch event teaser. We’ll have more information about the smartphone next week. Facebook Comments
